            h2 A Gift
            p A gift so personal is seldom given in humanitarian efforts. We all know how much we love to take and get photos of our families, children, and friends. Even in this digital age in the U.S. where we have access to images anytime, we appreciate and cherish the photographs we get to hold in our hands. Imagine what it would be like to get a picture if you had very few or none. The influence on each person and often their family is significant.
            i.fa.fa-4x.fa-arrow-down.c-next

        article.c-screen.u-clearfix.c-screeen--support
            h2 Your
                span Support
            p.c-quote All of this could have never been possible with out Polaroid! Will you partner with us? Your support and partnership has the potential to impact the global community for good on an immense scale as well as have profound global PR and social outcomes

            h3 Working together we can do more
            div.c-columns
                p Love Polaroids brought encouragement and shouts of love to all the people Ceallaigh came across. And we would love to bring this across the globe with Polaroid’s help! We recognize the great needs for water, food, health, and shelter that exists for many developing countries today and those projects are worthy of our funds as well. We also believe we are called to take care of our global brothers and sisters in other ways and that all of us humans, regardless of our circumstance, all fundamentally need love and encouragement and to feel valued and celebrated by our families, communities, and even strangers. What better way to do this than the gift of a Polaroid.
                p We hope you will examine this following partnership plan with great consideration. Your donation dollar would go extremely far. With no administration cost at all, Love Polaroids is able to put all support right into the action of giving away Polaroids to people across the globe. We also believe this can be the start of a great collaboration for years to come

            h3 The Need
            p Our greatest need to be able to continue Love Polaroids is resources - funding for travel costs and Polaroid equipment. To stay in line with our mission to celebrate all people groups and serve those in under-resourced communities, we strategically chose travel locations in 3 different continents - South America, Asia, and Africa. All are on the list of least developed and most impoverished in the world. Strategically we will travel to remote areas where electricity and especially photographs are scarce.

